text: Barrie John Unsworth (born 16 April 1934) is an Australian politician. He represented the Labor Party in the Parliament of New South Wales from 1978 to 1991. He was the 36th Premier from July 1986 to March 1988. Unsworth was born in Dubbo, New South Wales. ==References== Category:1934 births Category:Living people Category:Premiers of New South Wales
